<item>
            <title>[LU-9235] LNet: Service thread pid 13033 was inactive for 0.00s.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9235</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Following call trace appeared on one of OSS servers. Interestingly, it states &quot;inactive for 0.00s&quot; and &quot;pid 13033 completed after 0.00s.&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: LNet: Service thread pid 13033 was inactive for 0.00s. The thread might be hung, or it might only be slow and will resume later. Dumping the stack trace for debugging purposes:&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: Pid: 13033, comm: ll_ost_io01_044&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel:&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: Call Trace:&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffffa083dddb&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? ptlrpc_update_export_timer+0x4b/0x560 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ptlrpc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffffa0844f75&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? ptlrpc_server_handle_request+0x385/0xc00 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ptlrpc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffffa04cd4aa&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? lc_watchdog_touch+0x7a/0x190 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;libcfs&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffffa083d8d9&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? ptlrpc_wait_event+0xa9/0x2d0 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ptlrpc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffff81064c00&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? default_wake_function+0x0/0x20&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffffa08476fd&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? ptlrpc_main+0xadd/0x1770 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ptlrpc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffffa0846c20&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? ptlrpc_main+0x0/0x1770 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ptlrpc&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffff8109e78e&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? kthread+0x9e/0xc0&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffff8100c28a&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? child_rip+0xa/0x20&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffff8109e6f0&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? kthread+0x0/0xc0&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffff8100c280&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ? child_rip+0x0/0x20&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel:&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: LustreError: dumping log to /tmp/lustre-log.1476160288.13033&lt;br/&gt;
Oct 11 13:31:28 oss23 kernel: LNet: Service thread pid 13033 completed after 0.00s. This indicates the system was overloaded (too many service threads, or there were not enough hardware resources).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
